{
  "description": "Handcrafted retrieval eval set — 15 QA pairs with the source files the retriever SHOULD return in its top-K. Every expected_source_file has been verified against data/cleaned/manifest.json.",
  "notes": [
    "expected_source_files is a set of paths RELATIVE to data/raw/ that are relevant to the question. Retrieval returns chunks; we score at the FILE level (unique source_files in top-K vs expected).",
    "expected_keywords are heuristic keyword checks for LLM answers — not used by the retrieval metrics but useful if you want to spot-check answer quality later.",
    "adversarial entries have empty expected_source_files; a well-tuned pipeline should retrieve low-similarity chunks that the LLM then refuses to ground on.",
    "Categories: how-to, concept, keyword (exact-term), reference, adversarial. Balance is deliberate so we see where each retrieval strategy wins."
  ],
